asim Nunez** is at the floor with a 45.9, facing a right-handed pitcher (Peralta, F, SP_xERA 3.68) where park factors are a drag (-4%) and the pitcher's skill is a concern (-8%), though a slow SP delivery adds a small SB boost (+4%).\n\nThe most notable bench decision involves **Coby Mayo**. He scored a respectable 39.1, benefiting from the same strong park factors and favorable pitcher matchup as **Gunnar Henderson**. However, his projected batting order (#8) and a negative platoon advantage (-8%) ultimately placed him just below the 40.0 floor, keeping him on the bench to preserve game caps. It's also worth noting **Luis Robert Jr.** remains on the Injured List, removing a high-upside player from consideration. All players are subject to lineup changes, with **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**'s situation being officially pending.",
